---
description: Rails 8 conventions for the sample todo app
alwaysApply: true
---

- Prefer Turbo Streams over custom JavaScript for dynamic UI updates
- Keep all migrations reversible
- Use strong parameters (`params.expect`) -- never use `permit!`
- Use `bin/rails generate` for scaffolding rather than hand-writing boilerplate
- Keep the schema scoped to the todo app; do not import models or migrations from other projects
- Follow RESTful routing conventions, use `resources` in routes
- Use partials for reusable view components (prefix with underscore)
- Write tests for new features -- at minimum a controller/integration test
